MOSCOW, Dec. 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia reported 20,638 new COVID-19 cases in the past 24 hours, taking the nationwide tally to 10,499,982, the official monitoring and response center said Friday. Meanwhile, the death toll grew by 912, the lowest daily count since Oct. 5, to 308,860, and the number of recoveries increased by 40,692 to 9,463,919. There are currently 727,203 active cases in Russia, the center said, adding that the mortality rate stands at 2.94 percent. Moscow is the worst-hit region where 2,739 new cases were reported in the past 24 hours, taking the total to 2,030,744.  Enditem